title: Im unable to see mine or anyone else's match history.

replies.body: Is this happening in the Beta Client, Legacy Client, or on the League site?
League site but only on crome browser.

You may be running a specific addon/extension in Chrome that could be causing this. Since you're only seeing this in Chrome it's either an extension, [**crowded browser cache**](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/201752694-Clearing-Browser-History-and-Cookies), or a chrome issue itself. I'm glad you've found a workaround, though.

Let me know if you have any questions.

I have been seeing this lately as well and following everything you have said (Cleared all cache, Removed all extensions, Cleared temps on PC as well)

The Version of Chrome I am using is Version 55.0.2883.87 m (64-bit) (my one at work may be different though and that also has the issue)

What I have noticed is it redirects to the core History page (http://matchhistory.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/ ) but doesn't redirect to the Users page in match history.

Also seems to happen in Internet explorer, Edge, and Firefox as well in my case. Interesting.

Also attempted with disabling of all AV and Protection software.

Thoughts?

EDIT: Running windows 10 at home and windows 7 at work

Four errors appear while looking at the sites console from Chrome

1. http://riot-dradis-assets-oregon.s3.amazonaws.com/dradis-0.5.0-prod.min.js Failed to load resource: the server responded with a status of 403 (Forbidden)
2. uncaught ReferenceError: Dradis is not defined
    at analytics.min.js:4
    at HTMLScriptElement.<anonymous> (analytics.min.js:1)

4. X-Frame-Options may only be set via an HTTP header sent along with a document. It may not be set inside <meta>. http://matchhistory.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/
